msContents.summary: The first ten of a cycle of twelve metrical homilies retelling the history of the biblical patriarch Joseph, attributed to Ephrem of Nisibis.

author.name: J. Rendel Harris Collection (Quaker & Special Collections, Haverford College)

msItem.title: Tedmortā da-ʻbadtāh Mārty Maryam b-zabnā d-Māmon

supportDesc.extent: 138 leaves : 225 x 165 (200 x 135) mm bound to 226 x 165 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil added, upper left recto.

binding.p: Bright red leather over pulpboard; blind tooled sets of three crossing diagonal lines and frame; endbands in green and red thread.

origin.p: Copied by Marā bar Zāwārā from Tel Keppe, Iraq and completed on 22 October, 1886 (f. 136v-137r).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by J. Rendel Harris.
